# Requirements "What Changed" Update Rule

When implementing a feature or making behavior changes, always update the relevant requirements analysis document with a `## What Changed` section (or refresh it if it already exists).

Use the feature analysis file under `requirements/` that matches the task context (for example, `requirements/analysis_feature1.md`).

Minimum content for `What Changed`:

- Backend/API updates that shipped
- Frontend/UI behavior that changed
- Test/spec coverage added or modified
- Any docs/script updates needed to support the change

Completion criteria:

- Implementation is not considered complete until the `What Changed` section reflects the actual delivered changes.
